  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="1171766">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1171766/" class="title-link">这本书不错。</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1171766"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/try09/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1633344-1.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/try09/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">钉子</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar30 main-title-rating" title="还行"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2007-06-23"
      class="main-meta">2007-06-23 22:03:27</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1171766_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  哲学本身就很枯燥，能把哲学变生动是不容易的。这本书还不错，最让我喜欢的地方是，它总是把哲学的发展与其相应的历史背景结合起来。因为看这本书，使我对欧洲史有了兴趣。

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">0有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_1171766_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_1171766_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>





